~
For loops take a name to bind,
a start position,
an end position,
and the increment to apply at the end of each loop.

If you override the symbol, the new value is taken and no increment occurs.
~

for! {i i1 i100 i1} {
	print! i$
}

for! {i i100 i0 i-1} {
	print! i$
}

for! {i i1 i100 i1} {
	let! i 99
	print! "Prints once."
}
